name: Navajo stitched rug found in Oregon
description:
Southern Oregon focuses very heavily on the roots of Native Americans and their play on our state. They have been around for so very long, and because of this many of their artifacts are found inside old homes and shops around here. Though these are heavily reproduced and faked now, there are still quite a few gems that we are so lucky to have found. This piece is a Navajo stitched rug, which had multiple uses both as a blanket or saddle-lie for a horse. We prefer to use it as a table runner or wall-decoration so as to preserve the overall quality of the find. 

It features a diagonal pattern-style that keeps it timeless and creatively enticing. With neutrals and a pop of color, this Navajo find is truly a rare beauty.

name: Antique Antelope Horns
description:
Magnificently worn antelope horns, these are mounted to two steel rods that cross and are then mounted to a beautiful piece of reclaimed wood .

The antlers are very old and original. 

This item is considered a rarity and is only available for purchase in the United State of America.

name: Triple 7 Recycled Dark Heart Pine Cutting Board No. 2
description: Handmade in America by Triple 7 Recycled, these beautiful pine boards are the perfect touch for a kitchen. They add a lot of style and functionality! Easy to store and carry and use consistently!

name: Man Ready Mercantile - Throne Spray - Forest
description:
For those who take care of business, we have the greatest smelling air purifier; the Throne Spray made in the USA. It's a great sized glass bottle that lasts a good many times! 

The best part is that we have this available in a forest scent, rep the Pacific Northwest and American made goods with us! 

100% made in America

We have this available in two scents, CITRUS and FOREST. 
You can select from below to choose your option, or visit the citrus scent separately!

name: Antique No. 2 D-Lite NY. Lantern
description:
Worn in but not wore out, the D-lites have been around a long time and were manufactured in the USA mainly using beautiful tin or aluminum, light weight metals that do well with outside conditions. This is specifically a No. 2 D-Lite Lantern! Made in the USA. Glass intact! 
Would make a great display piece in a home or shop!

name: ADVENTURE tee
description:
One of our most popular designs, is the ADVENTURE campaign we did in a minimalist way, in the old design it sported "Adventure lives outside your tent." We took the bare minimum and put it into our Anvil-style tee shirts. Featuring 9 bold letters, this runs in a limited amount and comes in both men and women's styles. Venture on dears!

Information - Process & Shipment.

Each shirt is made to order, so when you purchase a size, we most likely will not have a different size to exchange with you. We are terribly sorry for this but it is how we felt doing business would fit both parties needs. The shirts are collected in small batch orders of 10 or less and are therefor purchased within a 7 day period. After which it takes at most two weeks for the shirts to arrive, for the purchases made in the United States the turn around is 3-4 weeks for an order to arrive. It will be 4-5 weeks time for an international order. We are working our hardest at changing our supplier and getting enough startup funds to build the brand further. Every purchase helps us meet that goal to help provide a better brand for you to purchase from. Thank you so much - 1924.

name: Orn Hansen reclaimed Italian Military wool blanket
description:
Get ready for the Fall and Winter by being cozy and comfortable. Take this beautiful and quite large Italian wool military issue blanket home and stay warm!

Ships Internationally

Measures 81" x 64"

name: 1940's - 50's M.S.A. First Aid Kit
description: M.S.A. or Miners Saftey Association was very adamant about remaining safe while in the mines. They were in charge of distributing and developing plans for evacuation and overall the grand safety of the workers in shafts around the United States. This first aid kit is nearly entirely original with the exception of the two bottom packages we believe to be used and replaced in the same time period with similar items. Each package visualizes through way of illustrations different scenarios and the way in which each package could help for those situations. From aspirin to bandage wrap, this is an extraordinarily rare piece for the condition it is in. Definitely a must for the collector.

name: Antique Ocean Diver's bag
description: This is one hell of a find, the diver's bag is used to hold rods and harpoons for underwater diving. Each is built with heavy waxed canvas, a heavy metal bottom and rim trimmed with leather and and a rope handle. We do believe this was marketed for the military according to a branding number which was stamped on the side of the canvas bag along with numbers also handwritten on the other. This is a great piece that is over 4 feet tall and would look great in a collection.

name: Wooden Typesetter trays - Type "A" Press
description:
Found in McMinnville, OR. We have a small lot of 4 wooden typesetter trays. These were used for metal type lay typically for newspapers. For those of you not familiar, in the old days newspapers had to lay our little pieces of wood or metal type (letters) that would make up sentences, articles and ultimately the paper. This set up would be put into a printing press, inked and then pressed onto paper where multiple copies could be produced with ease. Each of these type were stored in an organized way into the separate compartments as you can see here. These trays would go into a set of drawers. Most of these are damaged or destroyed over time due to excess use or fire, there are quite a bit around the world still found luckily, however the location of the trays are always different and difficult to certify. These were all found inside an old printing business in McMinnville, Oregon. Type "A" Press, a printing company that does letter press and die-cutting has paired up with us to salvage a few to those home or shop owners that are really looking for a piece of decor that can really spark up a conversation or stand out! Well here they are!

We will randomly send you 1 of the 4 starting with the oldest based on our stock!

As such, please select which one you would like in the "option" box above! We hope you enjoy this item for the home!

name: Original rare Navajo Water blanket
description: Water blankets were used as a symbolic gesture for life and for the use of homeopathic medicinal uses. They usually had the emblem of a bug or a dragonfly which symbolized the growth of life. This is 100% wool, and entirely original Navajo. It is not a reproduction or fake and was found in the Southern region of Oregon, where a lot of attention to history takes place, especially in preserving the Native Americans that are indigenous to this area. A large blanket measuring 93" long and 52" wide, with slight damage due to natural use of the blanket over the years, not from mishandle or inability to properly care. This is an extremely rare find.

name: W.L. Dumas MFG WWII 1943 pack board
description: World War II Military rucksack wooden pack board. These are great pieces of memorabilia for the home! Great for decoration, or even for the missing sack piece! You can find them all over, but usually the boards are the rare pieces! This one is in exceptional condition which has been given a lot of love and attention over the years. All of the original markings are there, with leather patches that outline the metal rings giving it a sturdy build! This is one of the nicest boards we have come across.

name: 1920's - 30's United States Forestry pack
description: The elusive and extravagant United States Forest Service pack. Believed to be in complete and original condition, there are few spots of concern; the straps that attach the bottom of the frame to the bottom of the shoulder straps are restrung using a military-style flat cord, we know for sure this was not used originally and was a make-shift fix. This can be fixed to better meet your expectations for travel and authenticity. The USFS has been around for quite sometime, since 1905 to be exact. So this is one of the first items built for the group to ensure heavy carry while remaining (to them) quite comfortable. All of the original cotton stringing in the back is still there, with some pieces slightly frayed. The pack has minor aesthetic issues however the USFS symbol is still completely intact with a beautiful fade. This pack has a large inside pocket, and two smaller pockets also on the inside. Brass plates are on the end of each piece of the frame and well, it just does not get better than that. Definitely one of our rare American-made items. Something to pick up quick!

name: Atelier de l'Armee Handmade weekender denim tote
description:
Another grand piece made in the Netherlands by Atelier de l'Armee, this large weekender tote features 5 shades of Japanese selvage denims, all are deadstock, making this a one of a kind bag. Inside is lined with deadstock cotton indigo chambray, and two more shades of Japanese selvage denims. The straps are made from 2 French Army leather rifle sling handles, the closure strap is also made from the same material. Note! Raw indigo denim is easy to bleed onto lighter materials! 

For exact measurements please email us at info@1924.us

Model info: Model is 6'2" with a thin build. 

INTERNATIONAL ORDERS: please contact us regarding the order for exact pricing on shipping.
